nit, should this be doSslHandshake like how it's afterSslHandshake() instead of afterSSLHandshake()?

Sure, seems reasonable.

ACK
Done
Do you need to start the timer before this is called?  You cancel it at the start of afterSslHandlshake().
Yep.  Good catch.  Not sure how I did both.
Done
Remove this if you do not need to start a timer in doSSLHandshake()
Resolving this, as we do need to start the timer here.
I think you want to call "self->waitAndRetry()" here instead so that you can try again as part of the retry flow.
Ack.  I forgot waitAndRetry wasn't part of DoClose.
Done
Do we not want to retry if the SSL init failed?
IDK, I pulled this from the original patch, but that's fair, that's probably not the behavior we want.  Will fix.

Ah, sorry, sslInitFailed means that we failed to construct the object, which is unlikely, and arguably needs a better error handling path.  Given that would be a different patch, I'm going to go with this one for now.
SGTM
You forgot to remove this.  waitAndRetry() will handle calling doClose().
Fixed.
